        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 6:48PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Wagon Mound, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wagon Mound.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 383 and 405.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
